President Obama has announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key Administration posts. Henry Claypool, the Executive Vice President of the American Association of People with Disabilities, will be appointed as a member of the Commission on Long-Term Care. Dr. Julian Harris, the Director of the Office of Medicaid in Massachusetts, will also be appointed as a member of the Commission on Long-Term Care. Carol Raphael, the Vice Chair of the American Association of Retired Persons (AARP) Board of Directors, will be appointed as a member of the Commission on Long-Term Care. Diana Shaw Clark, a freelance writer and philanthropist, will be appointed as a member of the United States Holocaust Memorial Council. Greg A. Rosenbaum, founder and President of Palisades Associates, Inc., will also be appointed as a member of the United States Holocaust Memorial Council. President Obama expressed his confidence in the abilities of these individuals and his eagerness to work with them in the future.